"language": "zht",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.15.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.15.2</span> 標題：無花果餅（poultice, fig cake）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： דְּבֵלָה, תְּאֵנָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： dveleth t’enim)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： μάλαγμα</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： malagma)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis16:12\">WIS 16:12</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>無花果餅是把乾無花果壓在一起成為塊狀。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>這種乾無花果塊可以直接吃（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">9.5 水果乾壓成的餅塊 (blocks of pressed dried fruit)&lt;REALIA:9.5&gt;</a> ）。乾果可以保存很長時間。人們偶爾也把無花果餅貼在皮膚的癤子或膿腫上面，以軟化皮膚，達到治療的目的。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在希西家得醫治的故事中（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a> ），目前並不確定當時人們如何使用無花果進行治療。希伯來文短語<em>dveleth t’enim</em> 的譯法有：「搗碎的無花果」（“mashed figs”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> ）、「壓碎的無花果糊」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"French Common Language Version (Bible en français courant)\">FRCL</abbr> ）、「無花果膏」（“fig-plaster”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> ）和「無花果做成的糊」（“paste made of figs”；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> ）。在無花果不為人所知的地方，翻譯者可以說「名為無花果的水果」，或者用當地某種既可以吃，又可以入藥的水果來翻譯這個詞。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Wis16:12\">WIS 16:12</a> 中，希臘文<em>malagma</em> 是指一種軟化皮膚傷口或瘡的敷布。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Traduction Oecuménique de la Bible (French, 1975)\">TOB</abbr> 所用的“ointment”（「膏油」）一詞有些不準確，而<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 所用“poultice”（「膏藥」）的意思含糊不清。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New American Bible (1970)\">NAB</abbr> 譯成“application”（「敷用藥」），這是一個可資借鑒的翻譯方式。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> 的翻譯是「繃帶」。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
